Sure. First, let's install the necessary dependencies:

```
npm install preact preact-render-to-string preact-helmet --save
```

Now, create a new folder named `src` in the root directory of your Astro project and create the following files inside:

1. `src/index.js`
2. `src/App.js`
3. `src/style.css`

Now add the following code to `src/index.js`:

```javascript
import { h, render } from 'preact';
import App from './App';

if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
  render(<App />, document.getElementById('root'));
}
```

Add the following code to `src/App.js`:

```javascript
import { h, Component } from 'preact';
import Helmet from 'preact-helmet';
import './style.css';

export default class App extends Component {
  render() {
    return (
      <div className="app">
        <Helmet>
          <title>My Astro Preact App</title>
        </Helmet>
        <h1>Hello from Preact!</h1>
      </div>
    );
  }
}
```

Add some basic CSS to `src/style.css`:

```css
body {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Oxygen,
    Ubuntu, Cantarell, "Fira Sans", "Droid Sans", "Helvetica Neue", sans-serif;
}

.app {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  min-height: 100vh;
  text-align: center;
}

h1 {
  color: #0070f3;
  font-size: 2rem;
}
```

Now, create `PreactApp.astro` in the `src/pages` folder and add the following content:

```jsx
---
import PreactApp from '../src/index.js';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <script type="module">
      import {hydrate} from 'preact';
      import {html} from 'astro/dist/internal/__astro_slot.js'
      import PreactApp from '../src/index.js';

      document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
        hydrate(html`<${PreactApp} />`, document.getElementById('root'));
      });
    </script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="root">
      <PreactApp />
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
```

Finally, update your `src/pages/index.astro` file to replace its content with the following:

```jsx
---
import PreactApp from './PreactApp';
---
<Layout>
  <PreactApp />
</Layout>
```

Now you should have a working Preact app with an Astro project. Start the Astro dev server with `npm run dev` and access the app at `http://localhost:3000`.

If you need more help or code, feel free to ask.

